 begriffenen Christentum und der griechisch-römischen Umwelt interessieren. Dem neutestamentlichen Zitieren der pagan-griechischen Schriften ist ein separates Kapitel gewidmet.  aHow did it happen that 2nd century Christian authors often cited or alluded to pagan literature? To answer this question, the study examines their works together with those of their predecessors. It shows that the literary practice of "ing pagan texts had strong roots in Jewish-Hellenistic writings as well as in some New Testament texts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChristian literature, EarlyxHistory and criticism. 0aClassical literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aAntike Literatur. 4aAntike Philosophie. 4aUrchristentum. 4aZitat. 7aRELIGION / Antiquities & Archaeology.2bisacsh  aEarly christianity.  aancient literature.  aancient philosophy.  acitation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104292680 cprintz978311043096740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311042913840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110429138423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110429138/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076251-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2015  aZDB-23-DGGb2015